name: farming
description: Only between 1.6%  2 % of the American workforce can be classified as being “farmers”.   Of that group, perhaps 25% have enough capital on hand to buy new or used tractors when they need to.  There are approximately 4.2 million tractors on farms and ranches across the United States. The average age of tractors is over 25 years, and some of the oldest models are the most popular.
